The paper deals with optimizing depth map coding in 3D video, which involves computer vision (CV) and graphics (GR) techniques. The proposed algorithm involves adjusting depth distortion within a set of allowable distortions, which is related to information theory (IT). The paper also includes simulation results, which suggests that it may fall under multimedia (MM) category.
